The paper proposes the use of adversarial autoencoder networks for detecting accounting anomalies in financial statement audits. This involves the application of deep learning techniques, which suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.AI and cs.LG sub-categories. The use of handcrafted rules and the need for interpretability also suggest that the paper could belong to the cs.CR and cs.DB sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of journal entries, which could also place it in the cs.IR sub-category.
